<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-301-844  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 301 844.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>T H E Journal (Technological Horizons in Education)  April 1989v16 n8 p77(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Teaching at the speed of light: the fiber-optic connection.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mielke, Angela; Phelps, Sandra D.; Schwartz, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Two Louisiana schools are providing Chapter 1 programming toparochial schools while meeting federally imposed sitelimitations.andP;  This is accomplished through an integrated learningsystem (ILS) that uses a microcomputer-mainframe network tocoordinate instruction in the respective schools.andP;  Students accessthe ILS through individual log-on procedures, the pace of theirinstruction is determined by their progress and their records areautomatically saved.andP;  The system uses an Apple-Corvus interface,and data transmission is accomplished with fiber-optic technology.andO;ILS has been well received and will soon be augmented byadditional remote terminals.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     EducationTeachingNetworksFiber OpticsComputer-Assisted Instruction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>